modules.description: Provides functions for parsing and evaluating arithmetic expressions, including handling operator precedence and parentheses. Works with abstract syntax trees and strings representing mathematical expressions. Used to implement a calculator engine and validate user input in a code submission system.

Provides functions to generate unique identifiers, manage input/output channels, and compile solution expressions into OCaml syntax trees. Works with location data, strings, and custom specification types to transform and wrap code structures. Used to dynamically create and inject solution code into larger programs during parsing or transformation.
